      "title": "Locking First Image",
      "properties": {
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {},
          "version": "7.8",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "# If using video and ref images\n\nTo LOCK first initial image all three ref must be plugged with the same initial image\n\nsource_video\nreference_video\nreference_image_0 \n\nAll must have the same image for i2v locking the first frame"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 2803,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -1790.1879901472523,
        -2716.991127808597
      ],
      "size": [
        464.3693871223177,
        449.5205033391935
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 1,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# markdkberry.com\n\n## INSTALL\n\ndownload the GGUFs to test but probably be faster with fp8 if you stick with it.\n\n**WanMOEKsampler** it came with it not the usual dual sampler approach I am used to seeing with WAN 2.2. I \ninstalled the Wan Moe Ksampler from here as the other one has a known memory leak that crashes Comfyui [https://github.com/Farstone3D/ComfyUI-SVIWanMoeKSampler](https://github.com/Farstone3D/ComfyUI-SVIWanMoeKSampler)\n\n---\n\n## SPEED TESTS:\n\n- 640 on long edge (2.39:1) was done in 11 mins for 81 frames\n\n- 832 on long edge (2.39:1) was done in 10 minutes 81 frames once I added in sage attn and chunk. but attempt at 241 frames was looking at 30 mins per model so 1 hour. \n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
